KwaZulu-Natal premier Willies Mchunu fainted after he asked to be excused while delivering his state of the province speech (SOPA). Mchunu reportedly asked the speaker if he could be excused and let MEC Sihle Zikalala to continue with the speech. After the premier was helped off stage, Zikalala who is the head of government business took over. ANC secretary Mdumiseni Ntuli said once Mchunu  has completed his exercises with the doctors he is set to return back to the SOPA before going home. “His condition is quite well. He is very jovial. I had a long discussion with him on the phone. He is waiting for medical doctors to clear him so he can return," Ntuli said.  Commotion moments shortly after KZN Premier Willies Mchunu collapsed on stage and plans being made to intervene. #KZNSOPA2019 pic.twitter.com/tSP6ZX3HaQ  